<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870417-0058 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Holiday Corp.</HL><DD> 04/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HIATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   HOLIDAY CORP., Memphis, Tenn., said it completed financing arrangements for its $2.62 billion recapitalization and agreed to sell its 50% stake in Residence Inn Corp. for $51.4 million. The hotel and casino concern said it completed a $1.22 billion credit agreement with 12 banks, led by Citibank. Holiday previously completed public offerings of $1.4 billion of senior notes and subordinated debentures, proceeds of which will go to fund a special $65-a-share dividend to be paid April 22 to stock of record April 16. </TEXT></DOC>